item.title: Jdk 5.0 or 6.0 wont load
item.dc:creator: @modbrian modbrian
item.description:
@modbrian wrote:

okay, go to http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp and download JDK 6 update 7. when you click download choose the platform your using (likly window) and language. the next screen will give you teh option of online or offline installation, you want the offline version (77.45mb) select it and download it. once its finished downloading, find it on your computer open it and it will ask to be installed again. instal it again and it will work.

but you havnt set your path for jdk to run your compiler. so dont be mad if the compiler doesnt work yet
